lead_paragraph: Iceland pulled off one of the biggest shocks in European Championship history when they stunned abject England 2-1 on Monday, leading Roy Hodgson to quit and sending the tiny nation into a quarter-final against hosts France.

headline.print_headline: Iceland Stuns England as Euro Dream Continues
